Wash and dry produce.

Halve @brioche buns{2} and toast until golden brown in a #toaster{}.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Slice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch rounds; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and @dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}.

Spread Dijonnaise on cut sides of toasted buns. Fill buns with @sliced turkey breast{8%ounce}, @gouda cheese{2%slices}, lettuce (we used two leaves per sandwich; save remaining lettuce for another use), and tomato. Serve.

> This is a far cry from your average ho-hum turkey and cheese sammy (although it still takes just 10 minutes to make). We've hooked you up with soft, plush brioche buns, hearty sliced turkey, and mild, nutty gouda slices. Simply whip up a quick homemade Dijonnaise to slather on the buns, layer with crisp baby lettuce and juicy tomato, and dig into a classic yet elevated sandwich you'll look forward to all morning.